now if you plan to go: Where to go The Detroit march begins at 11 a.m. at Rivard Plaza, 1340 E. Atwater, heads west along the RiverWalk, crossing Jefferson to head north to Campus Martius and then back south to the RiverWalk, where speakers will address marchers near the Renaissance Center, according to the event\u2019s Facebook page . Speakers are to include local students, Congresswomen Debbie Stabenow and Brenda Lawrence, as well as state legislators and others from activist organizations. Also read: B'ham church plans lock-in to prep for march Huge turnout expected More than 3,000 people have indicated on the event's Facebook page that they plan to attend the Detroit march and more than 8,000 people have indicated they are interested. There are other marches being held across metro Detroit Saturday, too. To find one, click here . Grab a Lyft Car service Lyft is offering free rides to March For Our Lives events across the country, including the one in Detroit. Click here to figure out how to get a free ride. \nLyft passengers and driver. (Photo: (Photo: Lyft).) Dodge traffic troubles Driving yourself? Remember there have been numerous road and lane closures for pothole repairs. Check MDOT\u2019s web site for updates. Here\u2019s information about the RiverWalk and Rivard Plaza, including nearby parking, from the Detroit Riverfront Conservancy. Under sunny skies Expect a clear, crisp day in Detroit Saturday, with a high of 39 degrees according to a forecast from the National Weather Service. CLOSE More than 1 million people are expected to attend the March for Our Lives in Washington D.C. hoping for changes to gun regulations and school safety. USA TODAY", "highlightText": "", "highlightTitle": "", "language": "english", "external_links": [], "entities": {"persons": [{"name": "michael schwab martin", "sentiment": "none"}], "organizations": [{"name": "facebook email", "sentiment": "negative"}, {"name": "vanderbilt", "sentiment": "none"}, {"name": "detroit free pres